##It's not an emergency, it's over."A Wuhan Union Hospital of relief supplies

Masks from home and abroad are being sent to Wuhan, but Wuhan Hospital is not only missing masks, even about to run out. People's Daily asked on its official microblog: Is there a shortage of materials or is there a problem in the distribution of materials?

Up to now, all materials received by Concorde Hospital are donated by enterprises and individuals. Materials directly to the local epidemic command or each hospital, is the most effective

This article first appeared in the southern people's weekly

By Yang Nan and Meng Yiyi, staff writers

Intern reporters he Peiyun, Nie Yangxin

Editors | Kuai Lehao and Zhou Jianping

The full text is about 3,216 words and takes about 8 minutes to peruse

Image courtesy of reader

The Wuhan Union Hospital has been asking for help. From January 23 to the present, fundraising letters in the name of Xiehe Hospital or individual doctors have appeared one after another on various popular and official websites such as Friendagenda, wechat, Douban and learning power.

In an interview with China Central Television, the governor of Hubei Province said that "the material reserves are sufficient" on the same day that concord and nearly 20 other hospitals directly issued a public notice on accepting donations. Since the outbreak of the epidemic, medical protection equipment throughout the country to Hubei. In the past eight days, thanks to the efforts of the Chinese people at home and abroad, China has imported 56.228 million masks and 738,000 protective clothing, which were sent mainly to Hubei and given priority to Wuhan.

On January 29, the hospital collected 3,000 protective clothing, 5,000 medical N95 masks, 8,000 surgical masks, 3,000 disposable isolation clothing and 1,000 protective masks. The next day, "Mr. Do of Concord Hospital, " who is identified as a neurosurgeon at the hospital, tweeted that hospital supplies "are not in an emergency, they are gone. ".

Liu Xin, who is in charge of the hospital's material management, told the southern people's weekly on January 30 that the hospital's supplies could last only a day and a half at most. Most of the department's materials are unable to cover, "one can not come out, only hard on. " Liu Xin said.

At present, the hospital sent 500 medical staff to fight in the front line of the epidemic, the daily need to consume thousands of masks. The four-hour replacement of the original protective clothing, the basic medical staff dare not take off. The glue of the protective clothing is disposable and once removed, it can not be used again. "Try not to drink water, everyone wears Adult diaper and doesn't go to the toilet, so you don't have to take them off, " a Concorde nurse told us. However, it is disappointing that the latest list of materials issued by the Wuhan Red Cross, as the new crown pneumonia designated fever clinic, one of Wuhan's largest Three-a Hospital, the hospital is not one of the Concord.

A concord doctor who went to Guobo in Wuhan yesterday to collect supplies from the Red Cross told us that they had somehow returned empty-handed. They tried to negotiate with the Wuhan Red Cross Society for two hours, not only did not receive any supplies, even had to be unloaded.

Another historical detail is rarely mentioned: Wuhan was once the birthplace of the Red Cross Society of China. In 1938, Wuhan became the center of the War of Resistance, the Red Cross Society of China was established in Hankou, with Robert Lim, the first Chinese Dean of the Peking Union Hospital, as its commander. That year, the Red Cross in Wuhan and the Chinese people in the flames of war in advance and retreat.

Where are the donations from the community?

It's not just the Union hospital that's not getting supplies. Yesterday, some other hospitals in Wuhan, as well as hospitals in Huanggang and Xianning, did not receive supplies. It was not until yesterday that the Wuhan Red Cross first published details of the distribution of supplies: Only 13 hospitals received supplies on January 30. At present, 61 hospitals in Wuhan have set up fixed-point fever clinic, 24 hospitals have been temporarily transformed into fever patients admitted to hospital, the shortage of materials is still very large. As of March 30, the Wuhan Red Cross had received 608.08 million yuan in anti-epidemic funds, 9,316 boxes of face masks, 74,522 sets of protective clothing, 80,456 goggles and other medicines and medical equipment, Xinhua reported.

Southern weekly called the Wuhan Red Cross. The materials that the other side promises to donate to the hospital by individuals and enterprises can be distributed to the hospital in a targeted way, but the materials that are not donated in a targeted way can be distributed to the hospital in a unified way by the Health Commission and the Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and control headquarters. Wuhan Health Commission Staff said that the hospital submitted daily needs to health commission, the specific allocation is still transferred to the Red Cross responsibility.

Last night, Li Qiang, a member of the party group of the Wuhan Municipal Government, confessed at a regular press conference on the prevention and control of the Hubei Pneumonia epidemic that the Red Cross Society's material allocation was not timely enough and needed improvement. At the same time, he pointed out that the current consumption is greater than supply, is the main reason for the shortage of hospital materials.

Meanwhile, photos and videos taken by several media outlets last night showed mountains of supplies at the Wuhan Red Cross warehouse in a hall of the Guobo Center in Hanyang District, Wuhan. Another user, named "Weibo Nuer, " posted a query on Weibo that the 9,840 pairs of medical gloves he had donated to Huangpi District Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine in Wuhan City were signed for on January 27, but Huangpi Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine has not received them. Three days later, repeated calls to the Wuhan Red Cross, the other side said, "too much material, there is no way to find. "

The Red Cross is now almost the only entry point for donations. The province requires that "donations to the province go through the provincial Red Cross Society and donations to Wuhan go through the Wuhan Red Cross Society" . But Chen Yun, executive vice president of the Wuhan Red Cross, said in an interview: the Wuhan Red Cross has only ten people, and the manpower is very tight. Although the municipal government has supported 30 people of the Statistics Bureau to do inventory and registration of materials, it is still "no way. ".

A number of private charities are also racing the virus at the moment. Taking the Han Hong Charitable Foundation as an example, the foundation daily announces the progress of the project of "Supporting Wuhan" . Seven batches of materials have already arrived in Wuhan and surrounding cities, nearly 300,000 surgical masks, 6,000 protective clothing and 50 blood gas analyzers are about to be issued.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
What are the standards for the distribution of materials under overall planning?

The day before yesterday, the Hubei Red Cross Society made public on its website for the first time the use of donated materials for the prevention and control of the new type of coronary pneumonia. The Union Hospital, which is in the front line and under great pressure to prevent the epidemic, also received only 3,000 masks from Ms. Han in Shaanxi. On the same sheet, thirty-six thousand N95 masks were sent to two Putian Department hospitals.

One of the hospital is not a designated fever patients admitted to hospital, the hospital attending gynecology, obstetrics and infertility, and so on. Last night, the director of the Yan 'Ai Hospital explained to the media: We are in an epidemic area, we can not ask the society for masks, we can not ask the city Red Cross Society for masks, we can only ask the provincial Red Cross Society for help. At present, more than 200 hospital staff have routinely consumed 12,000 of the masks.

The Wuhan Union Hospital has twice that number of health care workers on the front lines.

A day later, the provincial Red Cross Society said it had "reviewed the relevant information" and found that the published information was inaccurate due to work errors. Now "N95 mask 36,000" correction to "KN95 mask 36,000" , its flow to "Wuhan Renai hospital 16,000, Wuhan Tianyou hospital 16,000" correction to "Wuhan Renai hospital 18,000, Wuhan Tianyou hospital 18,000" .

KN95 can not be used to protect frontline personnel, so it was given to general hospitals involved in the outbreak, the provincial Red Cross said in a public statement.

In response to a question from southern weekly, the Wuhan Red Cross said that many of the supplies it received were substandard and could not be distributed to frontline medical staff. But a number of Concorde medical staff told the southern people weekly, some departments have self-financed daily substandard materials are the top.

Liu Xin told us that many of the supplies they received from various sectors also did not meet medical standards, such as industrial masks and industrial protective clothing. But these substandard materials are not wasted. second-line personnel such as hospital security guards or cleaners can use them. They fight every day on the front lines of triage, maintaining order and keeping the environment clean. They come into contact with large numbers of patients and medical waste, their safety is also important to ensure the normal operation of hospitals and control the spread of the epidemic again.

For the past 10 days, Concorde has been raising a little every day and using a little. Even basic materials such as 84 disinfection water, the entire hospital's storage is only 300 bottles at most, which is far from enough to cover the needs of the whole hospital. All materials are given priority in fever clinics, isolation wards and intensive care units, most of which do not receive sufficient supplies, and medical staff are forced to use garbage bags as shoe covers and goggles as local materials.

Wuda Northern California Alumni Association and Huakao Northern California Alumni Association jointly donated a batch of 2.5 tons of medical supplies to Concord Hospital

At last, the hospital received a donation from the people

Up to now, all the materials received by the Union hospital come from the donation of enterprises and individuals. Materials directly to the local epidemic command or each hospital, is the most effective.

Direct donations from businesses and individuals, streamlined in the middle, are the quickest way to get to a hospital. In order to save time, goods arrived in Wuhan, Xiehe directly sent a small truck to the high-speed checkpoints or airport to pick up cargo.

"To be honest, it's a bit of a Eight Immortals at the moment, " said a Concorde doctor. In a crisis, sometimes it's all about personal connections. Some of the doctors contacted friends to arrange supplies and donate to their departments. Some of the nurses contacted Shang Chao and donated a batch of rice boxes to the departments.

When the doctors of concord unpacked their supplies, they could often see the boxes that said, "the whole nation is with you, we must refuel. " "It's really touching, " said one of the doctors. He also wanted southern people to tell everyone that they really didn't need the ski glasses, even though they were in short supply. They are grateful to an unknown donor, but ski goggles are not medically viable.

After sending out a cry for help micro-blog, the hospital entered two big trucks and a small truck yesterday. There are not only medical supplies, but also food and other daily necessities. Of that, 2.5 tons were donated jointly by the Wuhan University and the huake Northern California Alumni Association. They included 200,000 surgical masks, 27,500 pairs of gloves and 4,000 protective clothing, which were taken directly to the hospital yesterday afternoon. The shipment, which was also supposed to be distributed by the Red Cross, was registered with the Red Cross by the donor, who, in view of its turnover efficiency, delivered the goods directly to the hospital through various communications and efforts.

However, these materials can not be fully supplied to the hospital, and will be distributed by the hospital to other hospitals such as Zhongnan Hospital and Tongji Hospital, which are also in a shortage of materials.

As of press time, there are Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital to the community sent to the information: "Not Urgent! Is Not! "

(Liu Xin is an alias)
